d EB-3 when EB-2 qualifications exist or vice versa.","fix":"Assess education/experience for optimal category","severity":"Common"},{"title":"Medical inadmissibility","description":"Health grounds not addressed.","fix":"Complete medical early; consult on waivers if needed","severity":"Medium"}],"faqs":[{"q":"Can we guarantee green card?","a":"No. Multi-step process with DOL, USCIS, and visa availability. Never promise approval or timeline."},{"q":"How long for Indians EB-2?","a":"Check current Visa Bulletin—often many years backlog. Dates move monthly."},{"q":"What is PERM?","a":"Labor certification proving no qualified US workers available—required for most EB-2/EB-3."},{"q":"Can spouse work during wait?","a":"Depends on status—H-4 EAD, L-2, or EAD with pending I-485 if eligible."},{"q":"What is priority date?","a":"Date PERM filed or I-140 receipt—determines place in queue per Visa Bulletin."},{"q":"EB-1 vs EB-2?","a":"EB-1 for extraordinary ability/multinational managers—no PERM. EB-2 typically needs PERM unless NIW."},{"q":"What is NIW?","a":"National Interest Waiver—EB-2 without PERM if work benefits US national interest."},{"q":"Family-based options?","a":"I-130 through US citizen/LPR relatives—preference categories have own backlogs."},{"q":"What is Description for this service?","a":"Lawful permanent residence (green card) via employment sponsorship (EB-1/2/3/5) or family petition (I-130). Multi-step process involving PERM, I-140, priority date, and I-485 or consular processing."},{"q":"What is Eligible applicants for this service?","a":"Qualifying job offer/sponsor (EB) or qualifying family relationship · PERM for most EB-2/3 · Priority date current per Visa Bulletin · Medical and character clearances"},{"q":"What is India backlog reality for this service?","a":"Indian-born EB-2/EB-3 applicants often wait years after I-140 approval for priority date to become current. Monitor Visa Bulletin monthly."},{"q":"Important note on India backlog reality?","a":"Indi